.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71"></path></svg></button></div></d=
iv></h3><p><span>Interestingly, Hirschman observes that as conditions in a =
society improve, their scope for deterioration increases. He describes it a=
s a =E2=80=9Cpenalty of progress=E2=80=9D that the better things get, the w=
orse things </span><em>can </em><span>get, because as society advances, it =
has a longer way to fall. In other words, economic progress positively corr=
elates with latitude for deterioration. &nbsp;</span></p><p>Which means mor=
e people may feel they must make the crucial decision: Voice or exit?</p><d=
